.TH LEXCONFIG l
.SH NAME
lexconfig \- configure the lexidata memory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lexconfig
[<configuration number>]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.I lexconfig
is a command that sets up the Lexidata memory boards according to 
configurations listed in the Lexidata 90 Reference Manual (page 48).
The configuration number defaults to configuration 9.
